data.text:
Brian McFadden is a former Westlife member, singer and songwriter and current reality tv star and television personality. Born 12 April 1980.

He has collaborated with Delta Goodrem on several songs (Mistakes, Hollow No More and Almost Here) and contributed heavily to her self titled 2007 album in multiple ways writing and sourcing songs, the muse for others, sourcing cowriters \ musicians, started a team called The Elements and was also engaged to her for 5 years, starting in 2007, They started going out in 2004 and ended their relationship for the final time in 2011 [1] [2] [3] [1] [4][5] .

He may have been the muse for Together We Are One, Believe Again, In This Life, I'm Not Ready, Mistakes, I Lost All Love 4 U , Control, Alcohol, Dancing With A Broken Heart, Hunters And The Wolves (The person she's making jealous), Encore, and Solid Gold but Delta is not one to confirm her muses. Delta was also the drive for his albums Irish Son(04), Set In Stone(08) and Wall Of Sounds (2010)
